# Frontend Architecture: Feature-Based (Vertical Slice)

Follow this structure for all frontend development in the `apps/mobile` directory. Organize code by business features rather than technical file types.

## Directory Structure

```text
src/
├── application/        # App-wide configuration & initialization (NOT Expo Router routes)
│   ├── router.tsx      # Navigation/Router setup
│   ├── store.ts        # Global state management
│   └── providers/      # Context/Global providers
│
├── features/           # Core business logic (Vertical Slices)
│   ├── [feature-name]/
│   │   ├── api.ts      # Feature-specific API calls
│   │   ├── [name].slice.ts # Feature-specific state
│   │   ├── components/ # Components used only within this feature
│   │   ├── hooks.ts    # Custom hooks for this feature
│   │   └── pages/      # Screen/Page components for this feature
│
├── entities/           # Domain models and logic (Optional)
│   ├── [entity-name]/  # user, product, business, etc.
│   │   ├── types.ts
│   │   └── ui/         # Entity-specific UI fragments
│
├── shared/             # Reusable, app-agnostic modules
│   ├── ui/             # Atomic components (Buttons, Inputs, etc.)
│   ├── hooks/          # Global reusable hooks
│   ├── lib/            # Utility libraries, formatters
│   └── types/          # Global TypeScript definitions
│
├── assets/             # Static assets (images, fonts)
├── styles/             # Global styles and themes
└── main.tsx            # Entry point
```

## Key Principles

1.  **Feature Encapsulation**: If a component or helper is only used by one feature, it should live inside that feature's folder.
2.  **Shared vs. Feature**: Only move code to `shared/` if it is truly generic and reusable across multiple unrelated features.
3.  **Cross-Feature Imports**: Avoid deep nesting imports between features. Features should ideally interact through shared state or the router.
4.  **Avoid Expo Router Collision**: Expo Router treats `src/app` as the **routes root**. Since our routes live in `apps/mobile/app/`, we keep app initialization under `src/application/`.
5.  **Avoid Type-Based Folders**: Do not use global `components/`, `services/`, or `utils/` folders unless the code is genuinely shared across the whole app.
6.  **Scaling**: This architecture is designed to scale as the app grows. Each feature should be self-contained enough to be understood in isolation.

